Source: mlxcel
Section: science
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jeongkyu Shin <inureyes@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               rustc (>= 1.85),
               cargo (>= 0.85),
               pkg-config,
               cmake,
               build-essential,
               libssl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/lablup/mlxcel
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/lablup/mlxcel
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/lablup/mlxcel.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: mlxcel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ca-certificates
Description: High-performance LLM/VLM/VLA inference on Apple Silicon and CUDA GPUs
 mlxcel is a high-performance inference engine for Large Language Models (LLM),
 Vision-Language Models (VLM), and Vision-Language-Action Models (VLA) on Apple
 Silicon and CUDA GPUs. It provides both a CLI tool and an OpenAI-compatible
 HTTP server.
 .
  * Support for 57+ model architectures (Llama, Qwen, Gemma, Phi, Mistral, etc.)
  * OpenAI-compatible API server (mlxcel-server)
  * Speculative decoding with draft models
  * Continuous batching for high-throughput serving
  * Vision-Language Model (VLM) support with image inputs
  * LoRA adapter support
  * llama-server CLI compatibility
  * Advanced sampling strategies (Top-P, Top-K, Min-P, DRY, repetition penalty)
 .
 Developed and maintained by Lablup Inc.
